Hard-Case-Lite-construction-2021-560x420.jpg 560w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Bontrager-AW3-Hard-Case-Lite-construction-2021-80x60.jpg 80w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Bontrager-AW3-Hard-Case-Lite-construction-2021-265x198.jpg 265w\"></a></p><p>But as they say, it’s what’s on the inside that counts. Thanks to a new aramid/nylon weave for the puncture protection layer under the tread, Bontrager claims the tire keeps its suppleness but drastically outperforms the last model. According to independent testing by Wheel Energy in Finland, the new AW3 Hard-Case Lite is 78% stronger in terms of puncture protection compared to the previous AW3 Hard-Case Lite tire.</p><p>As the name would imply, the Hard-Case Lite is the lighter of the two, but still features the Aramid/Nylon weave under the tread and a reinforced chafer for sidewall and bead protection.</p><p><span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-box-4\"></span>The AW3 Hard-Case Lite tires are offered 700c x 25mm/28mm/32mm/38mm with a 60tpi casing, folding bead, and claimed weights of 260g to 450g.</p><h2><span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-large-leaderboard-2\"></span>AW3 Hard-Case</h2><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Bontrager-AW3-Hard-Case-construction-2021.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Bontrager-AW3-Hard-Case-construction-2021.jpg\" alt=\"Bontrager AW3 Hard-Case tire construction cutaway\" width=\"1200\" height=\"899\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Bontrager-AW3-Hard-Case-construction-2021.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2